{% block content %}
  <div class="wrapper">
    <h1>Media object</h1>
    <div class="grid-wrap">
      <div class="grid-col tablet-grid-one-half">
        <div class="panel">
          <!---
          title: Media object
          usage: For displaying an image to the left of a block of content
          devnotes: >
            Classic [OOCSS](http://www.smashingmagazine.com/2011/12/12/an-introduction-to-object-oriented-css-oocss/) [media object](http://www.stubbornella.org/content/2010/06/25/the-media-object-saves-hundreds-of-lines-of-code/). The principles outlined in these posts underpin the approach to the development of this pattern library.
          -->
          <div class="media">
            <img class="media__img" src="http://fillmurray.com/100/100" alt="A handsome Bill Murray">
            <div class="media__body">
              Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit. Quis nesciunt sapiente possimus hic quibusdam deserunt ullam aut corrupti maxime debitis nisi culpa maiores rerum mollitia, soluta saepe asperiores quam aliquam.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel">
          <!---
          title: Media object with reverse image
          usage: For displaying an image to the right of a block of content
          devnotes: >
            [OOCSS](http://www.smashingmagazine.com/2011/12/12/an-introduction-to-object-oriented-css-oocss/) [media object](http://www.stubbornella.org/content/2010/06/25/the-media-object-saves-hundreds-of-lines-of-code/) with a twist.
          -->
          <div class="media">
            <img class="media__img--reverse" src="http://fillmurray.com/100/100" alt="A handsome Bill Murray">
